  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 Orthopedic — Tibial Tray FEA Credibility Assessment (MRL 3)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for finite element analysis (FEA) prediction of tibial tray stress and micromotion under physiological loading conditions for a Class II total knee replacement device. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can predict peak von Mises stress and bone-implant interface micromotion with sufficient credibility to support a 510(k) substantial-equivalence submission. Model Risk Level 3 reflects moderate model influence and moderate decision consequence. All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors are assessed; achieved levels meet or exceed required levels at MRL 3. Decision: Accepted.",
